# Dino Tamagotchi Development Plan

## Phase 1: Project Setup and Core Architecture

1. **Project Initialization**
   - [x] Set up HTML, CSS, and JavaScript files
   - [x] Create basic folder structure (assets, scripts, styles)
   - [x] Create start menue with just start new game
   - [x] Initialize Git repository

2. **Core Game State Design**
   - [ ] Design the game state object structure
   - [ ] Implement state management (local storage)
   - [ ] Create game loop mechanism

3. **Basic UI Framework**
   - [ ] Design main game container
   - [ ] Create placeholder for dino/egg display area
   - [ ] Add basic control buttons

## Phase 2: Egg Stage Implementation

1. **Egg Generation System**
   - [ ] Implement random egg type generation
   - [ ] Create visual assets for different egg types
   - [ ] Build egg appearance customization

2. **Egg Care Mechanics**
   - [ ] Implement egg warmth/care tracking
   - [ ] Create egg interaction mechanics
   - [ ] Build hatching conditions logic

3. **Egg UI Elements**
   - [ ] Design egg status indicators
   - [ ] Create egg interaction buttons
   - [ ] Implement egg animations (wobble, crack, hatch)

## Phase 3: Dino Core Systems

1. **Dino Types and Attributes**
   - [ ] Define dino species data structure
   - [ ] Implement dino generation based on egg type
   - [ ] Create base dino attributes and stats

2. **Core Status Systems**
   - [ ] Implement hunger system
   - [ ] Implement happiness system
   - [ ] Implement cleanliness system
   - [ ] Implement energy/sleep system
   - [ ] Create status decay logic

3. **Dino Growth System**
   - [ ] Design growth stages (baby, teen, adult)
   - [ ] Implement age progression
   - [ ] Create visual changes for growth stages

## Phase 4: Interaction Systems

1. **Feeding System**
   - [ ] Create food items with different effects
   - [ ] Implement feeding mechanics
   - [ ] Add overfeeding consequences

2. **Play System**
   - [ ] Design simple play interactions
   - [ ] Implement happiness effects
   - [ ] Create play animations

3. **Cleaning System**
   - [ ] Implement cleanliness mechanics
   - [ ] Create cleaning animations
   - [ ] Add consequences for poor hygiene

4. **Sleep System**
   - [ ] Implement energy management
   - [ ] Create sleep mechanics
   - [ ] Design day/night cycle (optional)

## Phase 5: UI Refinement

1. **Main Game Interface**
   - [ ] Design and implement status bars/indicators
   - [ ] Create intuitive control buttons
   - [ ] Add visual feedback for actions
   - [ ] Add Loading Button to load last saved from browser

2. **Notifications and Alerts**
   - [ ] Implement status warnings
   - [ ] Create notification system for critical needs
   - [ ] Add visual/audio cues for important events

3. **Customization Interface**
   - [ ] Create dino customization options
   - [ ] Implement accessory system (if applicable)
   - [ ] Design UI for customization

## Phase 6: Additional Features

1. **Achievement System**
   - [ ] Design achievement milestones
   - [ ] Implement achievement tracking
   - [ ] Create achievement notifications

2. **In-game Currency (Optional)**
   - [ ] Implement currency earning system
   - [ ] Create store for items/accessories
   - [ ] Design currency UI elements

3. **Mini-games (Optional)**
   - [ ] Design simple mini-games for dino interaction
   - [ ] Implement mini-game mechanics
   - [ ] Create rewards for mini-games

## Phase 7: Testing and Refinement

1. **Functional Testing**
   - [ ] Test all game mechanics
   - [ ] Verify state persistence
   - [ ] Check for edge cases

2. **Balance Adjustments**
   - [ ] Fine-tune status decay rates
   - [ ] Balance feeding/play effects
   - [ ] Adjust growth timelines

3. **Performance Optimization**
   - [ ] Optimize animations
   - [ ] Improve asset loading
   - [ ] Ensure smooth gameplay

## Phase 8: Finalization

1. **Polish**
   - [ ] Add final visual effects
   - [ ] Refine animations
   - [ ] Improve overall aesthetics

2. **Documentation**
   - [ ] Create player instructions
   - [ ] Document code
   - [ ] Prepare release notes

3. **Launch Preparation**
   - [ ] Final testing
   - [ ] Prepare deployment
   - [ ] Create backup systems
